Vendored from `romanz/electrs` (https://github.com/romanz/electrs):
  Version: v0.11.1
  Pinned commit: 35216c6d30148be8e6763d913d437330f431fc03
  License: MIT

Files literally vendored (top-of-file attribution headers in each):
  src/merkle.rs
    → electrum-proto/src/merkle.rs (Proof + Proof::create + Proof::to_hex
      block; satd-local helpers `compute_merkle_branch`, `merkle_root`,
      `root_from_branch` are wrappers, not vendored)

Files that follow electrs's wire shape but are reimplemented from
spec rather than literally vendored (we cross-checked against the
upstream source so the wire bytes match for every method we ship):
  src/electrum.rs    → electrum-proto/src/dispatch.rs + handlers/*
  src/status.rs      → electrum-proto/src/status.rs
                       (we reuse `node_index::status_hash`, which is
                       byte-identical to electrs's hash by spec)
  src/types.rs       → electrum-proto/src/types.rs
                       (only the wire-format types — `Height`,
                       `HistoryEntry`, `Balance`, `UnspentEntry` — are
                       relevant; electrs's DB-row types are not.)

Wire-format compatibility points cross-checked against electrs v0.11.1:
  - scripthash hex on the wire is byte-reversed (electrs uses
    `#[hash_newtype(backward)]`; we reverse at serde boundaries).
  - Electrum `Height` enum: confirmed → block height (positive),
    unconfirmed-no-deps → 0, unconfirmed-with-deps → -1. Affects
    `HistoryEntry.height` and the input to `status_hash`.
  - Mempool `HistoryEntry` always carries `fee` (sat).
  - `listunspent` merges confirmed and mempool funding/spending
    rows, matching electrs's `Unspent::build`.
  - `transaction.get verbose=true` mirrors Bitcoin Core's
    `getrawtransaction <txid> 1` JSON shape. Electrs proxies to
    bitcoind; we build the same JSON from satd's chainstate directly.
  - `transaction.broadcast_package` accepts an array of hex-encoded
    txs and reports per-tx accept/reject.
  - JSON-RPC batch requests (`[req, req, …]`) are accepted alongside
    single requests.
  - Error codes: BadRequest = 1, DaemonError = 2, internal = -32603.
    Error message strings match electrs's fixed wording where the
    code is fully spec-defined.

